---
# C ABI surface — overrides the project's C++ defaults for readability of the
# binding contract that external languages (Java/JNI, Python, Rust, …) wrap.
#
# Differences from the root .clang-format:
#   - Enums break onto multiple lines (one constant per line) — easier to scan,
#     trivial to diff when adding a new value.
#   - Consecutive declarations / typedefs align their identifier and trailing
#     comment columns so the opaque-handle block reads as a table.
#   - Pointers / brace placement / column limit inherited from the root profile.
BasedOnStyle: InheritParentConfig
Language: Cpp

ColumnLimit: 120
AllowShortEnumsOnASingleLine: false
AlignConsecutiveDeclarations: Consecutive
AlignConsecutiveAssignments: Consecutive
AlignTrailingComments:
  Kind: Always
  OverEmptyLines: 0
...
